Jeanmarie Simpson https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jeanmarie_Simpson 0 Jeanmarie Simpson (born November 20, 1959) is an American theatre artist and peace activist best known for writing and starring in the play and film, A Single Woman, based on the life of first US Congresswoman, Jeannette Rankin.
